The paper deals with efficient sampling of sparse and correlated signals, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The proposed sampling architecture and sampling theorem involve compressive sensing, which is a popular topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also mentions applications in array processing, which is a topic in signal processing (cs.SP) and systems and control (cs.SI).
